                          Measuring Health Effects

   Hazardous Substances Emergency Events Surveillance - a state-based
   surveillance system to describe the public health consequences
   associated with accidental releases of hazardous substances
   ATSDR Annual Reports
        2000 Annual Report
        1999 Annual Report
   National Exposure Registry - a listing of persons exposed to certain
   hazardous substances to help scientists understand how long-term
   exposure these substances may affect human health
   Guidance for ATSDR Health Studies - Presents the process used by ATSDR
   in considering health studies for communities that might be exposed to
   hazardous substances
